label.value: Total Clearance Predicted Normalized by Dose

value.value: The predicted total body clearance for intravascular administration divided by the dose.

label.value: Total Clearance Predicted Normalized by Surface Area

value.value: The predicted total body clearance for intravascular administration divided by the surface area.

label.value: Total Clearance Predicted Normalized by Weight

value.value: The predicted total body clearance for intravascular administration divided by the weight.

label.value: Volume of Distribution Predicted Normalized by Body Mass Index

value.value: The predicted volume of distribution associated with the terminal slope following intravascular administration divided by the body mass index.

label.value: Volume of Distribution Predicted Normalized by Surface Area

value.value: The predicted volume of distribution associated with the terminal slope following intravascular administration divided by the surface area.

label.value: Volume of Distribution Predicted Normalized by Weight

value.value: The predicted volume of distribution associated with the terminal slope following intravascular administration divided by the weight.

label.value: Volume of Distribution of Fraction Dose Predicted Normalized by Body Mass Index

value.value: The predicted volume of distribution of the absorbed fraction associated with the terminal slope following extravascular administration, where F equals the fraction of dose absorbed, divided by the body mass index.

label.value: Volume of Distribution of Fraction Dose Predicted Normalized by Surface Area

value.value: The predicted volume of distribution of the absorbed fraction associated with the terminal slope following extravascular administration, where F equals the fraction of dose absorbed, divided by the surface area.
A hypertensive disorder that develops during pregnancy.

label.value: Volume of Distribution of Fraction Dose Predicted Normalized by Weight

value.value: The predicted volume of distribution of the absorbed fraction associated with the terminal slope following extravascular administration, where F equals the fraction of dose absorbed, divided by the weight.
The quotient of quantities of trial subjects within treatment or control groups using an element of chance to determine the assignments, in order to reduce bias.
The determination of the amount of Chlamydia pneumoniae IgA antibody present in a sample.
The determination of the amount of Chlamydia pneumoniae IgM antibody present in a sample.
A lymph node located under the tongue in the floor of the mouth.
A tissue sample that contains mesenteric fat and peritoneal tissue.
A tissue sample that contains the body of uterus and the cervix.
The terminal part of the colon of the horse with a reduced diameter.

The ascending colon of the horse.
A non-Hodgkin lymphoma with an aggressive clinical course.  Representative examples include Burkitt lymphoma, mantle cell lymphoma, and angioimmunoblastic T-cell lymphoma.
The peritoneal fold that covers and attaches the ovary to the broad ligament.
A tissue sample that contains the epidermis, dermis, and subcutaneous adipose tissue.
The collection of words used by, understood by, or available for use by a person or group.
The body of words that a person recognizes and understands when read or heard.
The body of words that a person uses when speaking or writing.
The subjective property of a tone, determined by the frequency of the wave that produces it, that is perceived as highness or lowness.
A self-assessment to evaluate the perceived psychosocial consequences of a patient's voice disorder in terms of emotional, physical, and functional factors.
The process of producing vocal sounds by vibration of the vocal cords during an expiration of air.
A graphic record of the softest sounds that a person can hear at various frequencies, used to measure hearing loss.

Cases of harm to a child caused by parents or other caregivers, defined by the Federal government as: any recent act or failure to act on the part of a parent or caretaker which results in death, serious physical or emotional harm, sexual abuse or exploitation; or an act or failure to act which presents an imminent risk of serious harm.

A carcinoma that infiltrates the breast parenchyma.  The vast majority are adenocarcinomas arising from the terminal ductal lobular unit (TDLU).  Often, the invasive adenocarcinoma co-exists with ductal or lobular carcinoma in situ.  It is the most common carcinoma affecting women.
The unfair treatment of a person or group based on class or category bias.

A standard survey tool for assessing the parental resolution of conflict between parents and children, including nonviolent discipline and physical aggression. It consists of a 35-item self-administered questionnaire.
A standard survey tool for assessing the resolution of conflict between intimate partners. It consists of a 78-item self-administered questionnaire.
The activity or result of distributing or disposing of things properly or methodically.
A short or long-term association between two or more people, including kinship relations, romantic, business, and social interactions.
Surroundings or conditions that provide the means and opportunity to achieve physical and/or mental wellbeing.
A neighborhood or locale that provides access to healthy foods and healthy eating alternatives.
The extent to which one can make decisions and exercise control over their work.

The recognition that low neighborhood socioeconomic conditions have an impact on the services and opportunities available to its residents and have a wide and long-lasting effect on their economic, social and educational development. U.S. Census data can be used to determine the concentration of poverty at the neighborhood level.
The mental arousal or stimulation necessary to accomplish a task.

A social environmental measure of neighborhood race and/or ethnic residential segregation based on data from the U.S. Census Bureau.
A measure of linguistic development based on a person's ability to accurately repeat nonsense words.
A test that assesses a respondent's knowledge of grammar. It identifies respondents with specific language impairment (SLI) or other categories of language impairment.
A test that assesses an individual's understanding of spoken English language.
A test that assesses a respondent's ability to pronounce words accurately. It tests a respondent's word reading accuracy and fluency.
A molecular diagnostic test performed to determine the presence or absence of a BRAF V600K mutation in a tissue sample.
